      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">It is fairly common that a knock-out barrier option pays a rebate on a knock-out event to compensate the investor for the loss of the option. The rebate is typically a small amount and paid either immediately or deferred to the maturity. For knock-in barrier options, a rebate will be paid out at maturity if the barrier is never knocked in.</p>",
