    {
      "id": "/page/1/Text/8",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Another popular variation of double barrier is the knock-in option with a knock-out barrier. The knockin barrier option can be knocked out either before or after the option is knocked in. If the option can be knocked out even before the option is knocked in, this is called <i>knock-out dominant barrier option</i>. Again, this type of double barrier options provides more leverage than a single barrier option because it costs less than the single knock-in barrier option.</p>",
